## Summary
This documentation explains the Behavioral Offset feature in Amplitude, which allows segmenting users based on behaviors across two different time periods. It provides implementation steps for creating inline cohorts with behavioral offsets, including how to set rolling windows and offsets to identify users who performed specific actions across different timeframes.

